This paper proposes a framework for network navigation models using information theory and Markov decision processes. This work is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including social and information networks (cs.SI), information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
